{"lemma":"عِلْجُ","slug":"عِلْجُ","root":"ع.ل.ج","root_slug":"ع-ل-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ل-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n1092","n30196","n30197","n30198","n30199"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D9%84%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sturdy man, bulky bloke"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"atheist, kafir","tags":["archaic","slur"],"examples":[{"text":"إِنَّهُ بَلَغَنِي أَنَّ رِجَالاً مِنْكُمْ يَطْلُبُونَ الْعِلْجَ حَتَّى إِذَا أَسْنَدَ فِي الْجَبَلِ وَامْتَنَعَ","english":"It has reached me that some of your men would seek and chase a non-believer till he retreats to the mountains."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wild ass, onager"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Connected by Jakob Barth to Ge'ez አድግ (ʾädg, “ass”); as a nickname originating in some ancient dialect therewith inviting to draw a parallel with عَلَس (ʕalas, “emmer”) vs. عَدَس (ʕadas, “lentil”).\nThe word was quite obscure until the 2003 invasion of Iraq, when the Iraqi information minister Muhammad Saeed al-Sahhaf aka \"Comical Ali\" started frequently using it to refer to the invading American troops. It was a hassle for translators, and sparked debate in Arabic-language media regarding its meaning and etymology."},"ipa":["/ʕild͡ʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n1092","headword_ar":"علج","root":"Alk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":")] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA taEal~ajotu biEaluwjK","text_ar":"مَا تَعَلَّجْتُ بِعَلُوجٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not occupied myself in chewing with anything that is chewed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [And hence, accord. to some,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A message,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"communication sent from one person or party to another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, M, K, &c.; [in the CK, after"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~isAlapu","text_ar":"الرِّسالَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aluwku","text_ar":"الاَلُوكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained in the K &c., we find"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qibala Almaliki mu$otaq~N mnhu","text_ar":"قِبَلَ المَلِكِ مُشْتَقٌّ منهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which the first two words should be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyla Almalaku","text_ar":"قِيلَ المَلَكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in other copies of the K and in the TA; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAuluwku","text_ar":"الاُلُوكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put, in the CK, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aluwku","text_ar":"الاَلُوكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";]) said by Lth and ISd to be so called because it is [as it were] chewed in the mouth; (TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aluwkahN","text_ar":"اَلُوكَهٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, Sgh, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^olukapN","text_ar":"مَاْلُكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, Msb, K, &c.) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^olakapN","text_ar":"مَاْلَكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^olukN","text_ar":"مَاْلُكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, Msb. K, &c.:) accord. to Kr, (TA,) this last is the only word of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mafoEulN","text_ar":"مَفْعُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) but accord. to Sb and Akh, there is no word of this measure: (TA:) [i. e. there is none originally"},{"kind":"page_break","n":82},{"kind":"text","text":"of this measure:] other instances have been mentioned; namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makorumN","text_ar":"مَكْرُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuwnN","text_ar":"مَعُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEowunN","text_ar":"مَعْوُنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maqoburN","text_ar":"مَقْبُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maholukN","text_ar":"مَهْلُكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mayosurN","text_ar":"مَيْسُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which last occurs in the Kur [ii. 280], accord. to one reading, in the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fanaZirapN A_ilaY mayosurihi","text_ar":"فَنَظِرَةٌ اـِلَى مَيْسُرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but it is said that each of these, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^olukN","text_ar":"مَاْلُكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, may be regarded as originally with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or, accord. to AHei, each is [virtually, though not in the language of the grammarians,] a pl. of the same with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MF, TA;) and Akh says the same with respect to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"makorumN","text_ar":"مَكْرُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEuwnN","text_ar":"مَعُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) Seer says that each is curtailed of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"by poetic licence; but this assertion will not apply to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mayosurN","text_ar":"مَيْسُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as it occurs in the Kur. (MF, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aluwkN","text_ar":"اَلُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A messenger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K. [In the CK here follows,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wAlmA^oluwoku wAlmaA^oluqu","text_ar":"والماْلُوْكُ والمَاْلُقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but the right reading is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlmaA^oluwku AlmaA^oluwqu","text_ar":"وَالمَاْلُوكُ المَاْلُوقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as in other copies and in the TA.])"}],"source_refs":["ISd","Sgh","K","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30196","headword_ar":"عِلْجٌ","root":"Elj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sturdy, man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sturdy, and thick, big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse, man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any man having a beard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, L, Msb;) not applied to the beardless: (AZ, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beast"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is hardy, strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sturdy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an ass,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA,) in an absolute sense: (TA:) and, (K,) or as some say, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fat and strong wild ass:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fat and thick, big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse, wild ass:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, L, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulky, man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strong and big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulky, man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the unbelievers of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eajam","text_ar":"عَجَم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Persians"},{"kind":"text","text":"or other"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foreigners"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S, A, Mgh, O, L, Msb, K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of others;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L;) so called because of the thickness, bigness, or coarseness, of his make: (O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a strong and big,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulky, unbeliever:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) or simply"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an unbeliever;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb;) thus accord. to some of the Arabs, in an absolute sense: (Msb:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaAjN","text_ar":"اَعْلَاجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuluwjN","text_ar":"عُلُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilajapN","text_ar":"عِلَجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [quasi-pl. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoluwjaA='u","text_ar":"مَعْلُوجَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyuwxaA='u","text_ar":"مَشْيُوخَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoluwjaY","text_ar":"مَعْلُوجَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L, CK) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEolajapN","text_ar":"مَعْلَجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Sb, R, TA.) El-Hasan applied the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuluwjN","text_ar":"عُلُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", contemptuously, to certain men who neglected the supererogatory prayers before daybreak, performing only [afterwards] the prescribed prayers. (Mgh.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiloju maAlK","text_ar":"عِلْجُ مَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaA='u maAlK","text_ar":"اـِزَا=ءُ مَالٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is a manager, tender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superintendent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a good pastor, of cattle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camels &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilojN","text_ar":"عِلْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A cake of bread:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Abu-l- 'Omeythil, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cake of bread that is thick"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the edges"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the edge."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","L","AZ","S","K","TA","O","A","Mgh","CK"]},{"entry_id":"n30197","headword_ar":"عَلَجٌ","root":"Elj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small ones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young ones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of palmtrees. (AHn, S, O, K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalajaAnN","text_ar":"عَلَجَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."},{"kind":"page_break","n":2129}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n30198","headword_ar":"عَلِجٌ","root":"Elj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EulajN","text_ar":"عُلَجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~ajN","text_ar":"عُلَّجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) applied to a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sturdy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) in labouring, or striving, to prevail, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who throws down his antagonists much"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sir~iyEN","text_ar":"صِرِّيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in the CK, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaryEN","text_ar":"صَريعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and who labours,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerts himself, in performing, accomplishing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"managing, affairs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~ajN","text_ar":"عُلَّجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies a man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sturdy, in fighting, and in contending like the ram."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalijapN","text_ar":"عَلِجَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a she-camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sturdy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) or, so applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalijaAtN","text_ar":"عَلِجَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n30199","headword_ar":"عُلَجٌ","root":"Elj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~ajN","text_ar":"عُلَّجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalijN","text_ar":"عَلِجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the latter in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}